{
  "sections": {
    "gp_section_600495993288393573": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "af05f3837d15f815fbf143529bc2316f82de89c873ff02b98c3b533e4aaa8c2d_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg5GEPtDdEm_text": "<p>\"I was skeptical... but had to admit I was wrong. Spectacular! I waited 3 months to write this review because I wanted to be certain. The change in my neck and jawline is real. Not subtle—real. My daughter noticed. My ex-wife noticed. I noticed.\"</p>",
        "ggBQmFITqne_text": "<p>7,405+ 5-Star Reviews</p>",
        "ggFCrq--VDQ_label": "<p>&gt;&gt;&gt; START YOUR 8-WEEK TRANSFORMATION — GUARANTEED &lt;&lt;&lt;</p>",
        "ggJ7CWnSbN2_text": "<p>🇮🇹 Made in Italy | Pharmacist Approved | 60-Day Money-Back Guarantee</p>",
        "ggLi-VzMT-X_text": "<p>\"My wife thought I got work done. I was too embarrassed to tell her it was just a cream—I let her think I'd done something more dramatic. The change in my neck was that significant. What beef tallow promised, Omnis actually delivered.\"</p>",
        "ggMadLoh60l_text": "<p><strong>Robert, 62, Chicago</strong></p>",
        "ggNo8ZPr6EL_text": "Common Questions:",
        "ggQNYdLCjt-_label": "<p>START YOUR 8-WEEK TRANSFORMATION</p>",
        "ggURKlL77UO_text": "<p>I was quoted $9,000 for a neck lift. Decided to try this first because of the guarantee. I'm not saying it's the same as surgery—but it's enough. The sagging is reduced. I look less tired. I cancelled the surgical consultation. Best $70 I've spent in years.\"</p>",
        "ggZaYI9Amv9_text": "A final word from my pharmacy in Rome:",
        "gg_Ttq2kJj9_text": "<p><strong>How do I apply it?</strong> Once daily, at night, after washing your face. Apply to face AND neck—don't forget the neck. Takes approximately 30 seconds. No complicated routine required.</p><p><br><strong>Will it feel greasy?</strong> No. The formulation absorbs completely within 60-90 seconds. You won't feel residue on your pillow. This was a specific design requirement—Italian men don't tolerate greasy skincare any more than American men do.</p><p><br><strong>What if I have sensitive skin?</strong> Retinyl Palmitate was specifically chosen because it's gentler than standard Retinol. The formulation is dermatologically tested for sensitive skin. If you've had reactions to harsh Retinol products before, this is the alternative.</p><p><br><strong>When will I see results?</strong> Initial improvements in texture and hydration: Week 1-2. Visible structural firming in the neck and jawline: Week 6-8. This timeline is based on collagen synthesis biology and cannot be accelerated.</p><p><br><strong>Is there a subscription?</strong> No. This is a one-time purchase. No auto-ship, no recurring charges, no \"cancel before you're charged\" games. If you want more after your first two bottles, you order more. If you don't, you don't. Transactional integrity.</p><p><br><strong>What if it doesn't work for me?</strong> Request a refund within 60 days. Full refund, no questions beyond basic verification. The guarantee exists specifically because the company is confident most men will see results.</p>",
        "gg_gLeAjaKd_text": "<p>\"I have weird sun spots on my face and my neck was sagging badly. The spots faded within 2 weeks, but the real change was by week 6—my neck looked tighter, more defined. My collar fits better. I stand differently now.\"</p>",
        "ggfz4834Q_0_text": "<p>I've spent 23 years watching men struggle with something that shouldn't be this complicated.</p><p><br>The science of skin aging is well understood. The mechanisms that reverse it are established. The formulations that work have existed for decades.</p><p><br>The problem has never been knowledge. It's been access—and the courage to try something different after being disappointed so many times.</p><p><br>If your neck bothers you every time you look in the mirror... if you've started avoiding certain angles in photographs... if you feel like your outside no longer matches your inside...</p><p><br>You don't have to accept that.</p><p><br>The Italian Protocol exists. It works for most men who commit to the full 8 weeks. And with the guarantee, there's no financial risk in finding out if you're one of them.</p><p><br><strong>The only risk is spending another year watching the problem get worse.</strong></p><p><br>I hope you'll make the decision that's right for you.</p><p><br><i>— Dr. Marco Bianchi Pharmacist, Rome 23 years of practice</i></p>",
        "gggDVlmhqVN_text": "<p><strong>🇮🇹 Made in Italy | Approved by Italian Pharmacists | 60-Day Money-Back Guarantee</strong></p>",
        "ggp24cAQofs_text": "<p><strong>Francesco T.</strong></p>",
        "ggpjfDgc9SO_label": "<p>&gt;&gt;&gt; CLAIM YOUR U.S. LAUNCH DISCOUNT &lt;&lt;&lt;</p>",
        "ggrJm0VeaHu_text": "<p><strong>Vic</strong></p>",
        "ggupzjSgF9p_text": "<p><strong>Luigi M.</strong></p>",
        "ggxqYRBw5LI_text": "<p>No subscription. No auto-ship. One-time purchase.</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-600495993288393573"
    },
    "gp_section_600495993288459109": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "5bfe539b008af6af6c629ecd499abf9dc8b5ed13bbfd4ad4324d51747215e9a8_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg0CX8YCOpf_label": "<p>Privacy Policy</p>",
        "gg0m1EBaUNX_text": "<p>|</p>",
        "gg5V5V-ZkBR_label": "<p>Contact Us</p>",
        "ggOKnR2Om-W_text": "<p>The information provided on this page is for educational purposes and should not be construed as medical advice. Individual results may vary based on skin type, consistency of use, and biological factors. If you have specific dermatological conditions, consult with a healthcare provider before beginning any new skincare regimen. Dr. Marco Bianchi's recommendations are based on his professional experience and review of the Omnis Uomo formulation.</p>",
        "ggZ2KJWr6LK_text": "<p>|</p>",
        "gglQGEMIDyz_label": "<p>Terms of Service</p>",
        "ggv6XQMTT4u_text": "<p>© 2025 Omnis Uomo | Made in Italy 🇮🇹</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-600495993288459109"
    },
    "gp_section_600495993288524645": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "0536fb29015ed9d4e455a9032f4fc0c6901d68619498d69a7c82fc447e47ca83_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg-s1U-a7ON_text": "<p>In Italy, the pharmacy is different from what you have in America.</p><p><br>We don't just fill prescriptions and sell candy bars. Italian pharmacists are trained as frontline healthcare advisors. People come to us first—before the doctor—for skin conditions, digestive issues, sleep problems... and yes, aging.</p><p><br>Over the past two decades, I've counseled thousands of men about their skin. And I've noticed something peculiar:</p><p><br><strong>When American tourists come into my pharmacy asking for anti-aging advice, they always ask the same question:</strong></p>",
        "gg04un1EaV4_text": "<p><strong>I'm writing this for a specific type of man. You'll know if this is for you:</strong></p>",
        "gg1mNq57ffX_text": "<p>The most powerful product in the world is useless if you quit after a week because your face is peeling off.</p>",
        "gg2tIVaQMN6_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#FFD800;font-size:30px;\">2.</span> Something gentle enough to use consistently</p>",
        "ggAPKnnAGTy_text": "<p>In the past two years, I've seen a strange trend among American men: beef tallow.</p><p><br>They come into my pharmacy asking about it. \"It's what our grandfathers used,\" they tell me. \"It's all natural. No chemicals.\"</p><p><br>I try to be diplomatic. But inside, I'm shaking my head.</p><p><br>Here's the truth about beef tallow: <strong>It's passive.</strong></p><p><br>Tallow is an occlusive. That means it sits on TOP of your skin and creates a barrier. It prevents moisture from escaping. That's all it does.</p><p><br>It doesn't penetrate. It doesn't signal your cells to do anything. It doesn't stimulate collagen production.</p><p><br>It's like putting a tarp over a crumbling building. The collapse continues underneath—you just can't see it as clearly.</p><p><br>And that's the best-case scenario.</p><p><br>The worst case? Tallow is highly comedogenic. It clogs pores. I've seen men come in with cystic acne along their jawline after using it for months. Men who hadn't had acne since they were teenagers.</p><p><br>Plus—and I say this delicately—<strong>it smells like a steakhouse.</strong> Your wife will not appreciate it. Neither will your pillowcase.</p><p><br>There's a reason Italian pharmacies don't stock beef tallow. It's not medicine. It's cooking fat.</p>",
        "ggAqfECSQ3Y_text": "<p>It ages faster than the rest of your face.</p><p><br>The skin on your neck is thinner. It has fewer oil glands. It gets less attention, less protection, less care.</p><p><br>And after 50? The collagen loss accelerates dramatically in this area. The underlying structure collapses. Gravity takes over.</p><p><br>You wake up one morning and suddenly there's this... <i>looseness</i>... that wasn't there before.</p><p><br>Most men don't even notice it happening. Until they see a photo from their daughter's wedding. Or catch their reflection in a Zoom call. Or a colleague makes a comment about them \"looking tired.\"</p><p><br>Then they panic. They buy whatever cream promises \"younger skin.\" They slather it on their face.</p><p><br><strong>And they completely ignore the neck.</strong></p><p><br>That's mistake #1. But it's not the only one.</p>",
        "ggAvlCP674P_text": "<p><i>\"What can I do about these wrinkles?\"</i></p>",
        "ggCNYyuVOIk_text": "<p>If that sounds familiar, keep reading. Because what I'm about to share took me over two decades to fully understand—and it explains why the American skincare industry has been failing men like you for years.</p>",
        "ggCjS8yomP__text": "<p><strong>Let me be direct with you.</strong></p><p><br>The American skincare industry doesn't understand men over 50. Or worse—they understand you perfectly, and they're exploiting your desperation.</p><p><br>They know you'll buy whatever promises \"younger skin.\" They know you don't have time to research ingredients. They know you'll try something for a few weeks, see no results, and move on to the next product.</p><p><br><strong>That cycle is their business model.</strong></p><p><br>They don't need to fix your neck. They just need to sell you hope in a jar.</p><p><br>Here's what I've seen fail, over and over again:</p>",
        "ggG2lm4gsWE_text": "<p>\"Stop buying products designed for women. Stop chasing trends. Stop believing that 'natural' automatically means 'effective.'\"</p><p><br>\"Your neck needs a specific type of intervention. One that Italian men have been using for years—quietly, without fanfare, while American companies were busy repackaging the same basic moisturizers.\"</p><p><br>\"Would you like to know what we recommend?\"</p><p><br>Most of them lean in at this point. Because they've tried everything else. And they're finally ready to listen.</p>",
        "ggGRLaXWjf__text": "<p>Not surface-level moisture. Deep, cellular signaling that tells your fibroblasts to start building new collagen scaffolding again.</p>",
        "ggJGmufQXsg_text": "Thinking moisturizer is the answer",
        "ggLWhXFfn6S_text": "Italian Pharmacist Reveals: <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">The #1 Sign That Makes Men Look \"Old\" Isn't Wrinkles</span>—It's Something Most Products Completely Ignore",
        "ggNDR3HvJwm_text": "Mistake #1:",
        "ggNeqzC4IAz_text": "<p>This is the most common mistake I see.</p><p><br>A man notices his neck is sagging. He walks into CVS or Walgreens. He grabs a bottle of Nivea or CeraVe or whatever his wife uses. He applies it every night for a month.</p><p><br>Nothing changes.</p><p><br>Here's why: <strong>Moisturizers don't rebuild structure. They just add water.</strong></p><p><br>Think of your skin like a building. Collagen is the steel framework—the scaffolding that holds everything up. When that framework weakens, the building sags.</p><p><br>A moisturizer is like giving that building a fresh coat of paint. It might look slightly better on the surface. But the structure is still collapsing underneath.</p><p><br><strong>Your neck isn't dry. It's structurally compromised.</strong></p><p><br>No amount of hydration will fix that.</p>",
        "ggPEGV--92o_text": "This is what I tell the American men who visit my pharmacy:",
        "ggPSkDsU9AU_text": "The Retinol disaster",
        "ggQFv0ZZ8m__text": "<p>Most men don't know this: there are enzymes in your skin called MMPs that actively break down collagen. If you're building new collagen but not protecting it, you're running on a treadmill.</p>",
        "ggSdZqFlz3Q_text": "The #1 thing that makes a man look \"old\" isn't wrinkles. It's the neck.",
        "ggTPUqTHDTg_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#FFD800;font-size:30px;\">3.</span> Something that protects the collagen you're building</p>",
        "ggWXljIZlpy_text": "<p>After 23 years, I've identified exactly three things a man's aging neck actually needs:</p>",
        "ggZqmrDuyV7_text": "The \"quick fix\" fantasy",
        "ggcxLYLma-y_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#FFD800;font-size:30px;\">1.</span> Something that restarts collagen production</p>",
        "ggdcISJ7MsW_text": "My name is Dr. Marco Bianchi. I've been a pharmacist in Rome for 23 years.",
        "gggBa_bfd_f_text": "<p>Some men skip the creams entirely and go straight to the dermatologist's office.</p><p><br>Botox. Fillers. Laser treatments. Neck lifts.</p><p><br>I understand the appeal. You want results now. You have the money. Why not just fix it directly?</p><p><br>Here's what they don't tell you:</p>",
        "gggxdU3Lhmz_text": "<p>I'm not saying these options are wrong for everyone. But they're not the first step. They're the last resort.</p><p><br><strong>The first step is rebuilding the structural foundation. If you don't do that, nothing else matters.</strong></p>",
        "ggjpPQS5l0N_text": "<p>Now, here's where things get complicated.</p><p><br>Retinol—Vitamin A—is actually one of the few ingredients proven to rebuild collagen. The science is solid. Dermatologists have been recommending it for decades.</p><p><br>So why do I call it a \"mistake\"?</p><p><br>Because <strong>most Retinol products are too harsh for men over 50.</strong></p><p><br>Let me explain.</p><p><br>Pharmaceutical-grade Retinol works by forcing rapid cell turnover. It essentially tells your skin: \"Shed faster.</p><p>&nbsp;Rebuild faster.\"</p><p><br>In theory, this sounds great. In practice? For a man in his 50s or 60s with thinner, more sensitive skin?</p><p><br>It's a disaster.</p><p><br>I've seen it dozens of times. A man starts using a Retinol cream he bought online. Within a week, his face is red.</p><p>&nbsp;Peeling. Burning. Flaking skin everywhere.</p><p><br>He looks like he stuck his face in a furnace.</p><p><br>And the neck area? Even worse. The skin there is more delicate. It reacts more severely.</p><p><br>So what does he do? He stops using the product. Goes back to his useless moisturizer. And tells himself that \"anti-aging stuff doesn't work.\"</p><p><br><strong>The problem wasn't the concept. It was the execution.</strong></p><p><br>He needed the collagen-rebuilding benefits of Vitamin A. But he needed it in a form his skin could actually tolerate.</p>",
        "gglocQE8MOC_text": "So what actually works?",
        "ggmR7qlD9g7_text": "<p>Find a formulation that does all three, and you'll see results. Real, visible, structural results.</p><p><br>Ignore any one of them, and you'll keep wasting money on products that don't work.</p>",
        "ggp4c0exzuk_text": "<p>After 23 years dispensing skincare in Rome, I finally understand why American men spend billions on anti-aging products... and still look older every year.</p>",
        "ggpUJXtvv0K_text": "Here's what nobody tells you about the neck:",
        "ggq-t6w_CuD_text": "<p>They point to their forehead. Their crow's feet. The lines around their mouth.</p><p><br>And every time, I have to stop myself from saying what I'm actually thinking:</p><p><br><i>\"Signore... the wrinkles aren't your problem.\"</i></p>",
        "gguK3LI7g_4_text": "Mistake #3:",
        "ggvT_YFocyi_text": "Mistake #2:",
        "ggwY3K1iKUH_text": "<p>This may surprise you. It surprised me too, when I first started noticing the pattern.</p><p><br>But after 23 years of studying faces—thousands of them—I can tell you with absolute certainty:</p><p><br><strong>A man can have wrinkles on his forehead and still look distinguished, vital, even handsome.</strong></p><p><br>But a man with a sagging neck? A soft, undefined jawline? Loose skin hanging below the chin?</p><p><br>He looks old. Tired. Like he's given up.</p><p><br>It doesn't matter how expensive his suit is. Doesn't matter how fit his body is. Doesn't matter how sharp his mind is.</p><p><br><strong>The neck tells a different story. And people believe what they see.</strong></p><p><br>I call it <i>\"il collo del tacchino\"</i>—the turkey neck. And it's the silent killer of a man's presence.</p>",
        "ggwd0ezZK1I_text": "Mistake #4:",
        "ggxR9A0IYC8_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Botox doesn't work on sagging skin.</strong> Botox paralyzes muscles—it's designed for expression lines, not structural collapse. Your neck isn't sagging because of muscle movement. It's sagging because the collagen framework has degraded.</p>",
        "ggxR9A0IYC8_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Fillers are temporary and expensive.</strong> You're looking at $500-2,000 per treatment, every 6-12 months. And if it's done poorly? You get that puffy, \"pillow face\" look that screams \"I've had work done.\"</p>",
        "ggxR9A0IYC8_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Surgical neck lifts work, but...</strong> You&#039;re talking $5,000-15,000. Weeks of recovery. Potential complications. And even then, without ongoing collagen support, the sagging will return within a few years.</p>",
        "ggxbKd_nKvq_text": "<p><i>After 23 years, I've seen every \"solution\" the skincare industry has thrown at men. Most of them are useless. Some are actively harmful.</i></p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_0": "<p>You catch your reflection in a window or car mirror and think \"when did my neck start looking like that?\"</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_1": "<p>You've started wearing higher collars, buttoning that extra button, or avoiding certain angles in photos</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_2": "<p>You look \"tired\" even after a full night's sleep—and people have started commenting on it</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_3": "<p>You've tried moisturizers, maybe even some expensive creams, and nothing seems to change the sagging along your jawline</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_4": "<p>You&#039;re skeptical of the skincare industry—you&#039;ve seen too many promises and not enough results</p>",
        "ggzjOnDH5mr_text": "The \"ancestral\" trap",
        "section_preload": "true"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-600495993288524645"
    },
    "gp_section_600495993288590181": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "497d12244e1165c9a8de46c099d63ef32dbca21be3d2c0f47079037f9fdddda6_1_1_1_0__1",
