    "gp_section_600500557395788437": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "a636eeece5996a2c4a886774b38c9858e1bd1fcf231f005b7b955549d93324c6_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg0EcHm2YAu_text": "The breakthrough: <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Retinyl Palmitate</span>",
        "gg2-jiY6j6b_text": "But Retinyl Palmitate alone isn't enough.",
        "gg2EGqLyoP2_text": "<p>When men tell me their neck \"responded faster\" than their face, this is why. The neck shows structural changes more readily because there's less between the surface and the scaffolding underneath.</p>",
        "gg3ZElSJ2x7_text": "<p>This isn't marketing. It's pharmaceutical science. And we've had decades to refine it.</p><p><br>Walk into any pharmacy in Rome, Milan, or Florence. Ask the pharmacist what he recommends for a man over 50 concerned about his neck.</p><p><br>You won't hear about moisturizers. You won't hear about beef tallow. You won't hear about harsh prescription Retinol.</p><p><br>You'll hear about something else entirely.</p>",
        "gg4kNbQ0iOE_text": "In Italy, we've approached men's aging differently for generations.",
        "gg5Sm_WoNZ7_text": "<p>This is the primary signal. It tells your cells to produce new collagen. Without this, nothing else matters—you're just moisturizing a collapsing structure.</p>",
        "gg6J8ky7lD8_text": "<p>While American companies were busy slapping \"FOR MEN\" labels on women's moisturizers and calling it innovation, Italian pharmaceutical labs were asking a different question:</p>",
        "gg9UZj1vo5U_text": "<p>The key difference? <strong>The conversion happens gradually, inside your skin.</strong></p><p><br>You get the same collagen-rebuilding benefit as harsh Retinol. But because the active compound is being released slowly, over time, there's no \"purge.\" No redness. No peeling. No embarrassing flaking at the office.</p><p><br>I call it <i>\"il retinolo del gentiluomo\"</i>—the gentleman's Retinol.</p>",
        "ggB1e6dCzij_text": "<p>Once inside, your skin's own enzymes convert Retinyl Palmitate into Retinol, then into Retinaldehyde, and finally into Retinoic Acid—the active compound that signals collagen production.</p>",
        "ggCQZPk0vw5_text": "<p>Function: Restarts collagen production at the cellular level</p>",
        "ggDphhZB9yI_text": "Why this matters specifically for the neck:",
        "ggEiSospYEG_text": "<p>3. THE PROTECTOR:</p>",
        "ggF2D0jNb6w_text": "<p>Retinyl Palmitate is what we call a \"pro-drug\" or precursor. It's not the active form of Vitamin A—it's one step removed.</p><p><br>Here's what happens when you apply it to your skin:</p>",
        "ggJZWJHbFDq_text": "<p>This is the philosophy behind Italian anti-aging formulation. It's not enough to stimulate. You must also protect.</p><p><br>American products typically focus on one or the other. They'll give you a Retinol product (stimulation) and tell you to use a separate moisturizer (protection). Two products. Two price tags. Two opportunities for something to go wrong.</p><p><br>Italian pharmaceutical tradition combines them into a single, synergistic formula. One application. One ritual. Complete intervention.</p><p><br>And we apply it at night—when your skin's natural repair processes are most active. The circadian rhythm of cellular regeneration peaks between 11pm and 2am. That's when your skin is primed to receive these signals.</p><p><br><strong>This isn't complicated. It's just correct.</strong></p>",
        "ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Thinner epidermis </strong>— Gentler formulations absorb more efficiently without irritation</p>",
        "ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Fewer sebaceous glands</strong> — Won't get clogged by heavy occlusives like beef tallow</p>",
        "ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_2": "<p><strong>High MMP activity</strong> — Benefits significantly from the protective Hyaluronic Acid component</p>",
        "ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_3": "<p><strong>Visible structural framework </strong>— Responds dramatically to collagen rebuilding because there&#039;s less fat obscuring the underlying structure</p>",
        "ggRO6euQIIk_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 4:</span> Rebuilding</p>",
        "ggRUTFSviA9_text": "<p>Stabilized Vitamin C</p>",
        "ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_0": "<p><strong>72,000+ Italian men</strong> have used this formulation</p>",
        "ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_1": "<p><strong>7,405+ verified reviews </strong>with an average rating of 4.8 out of 5 stars</p>",
        "ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_2": "<p><strong>#1 pharmacist recommendation </strong>for men's anti-aging in Italian pharmacies</p>",
        "ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_3": "<p><strong>93% of users </strong>report visible improvement in skin firmness by week 8</p>",
        "ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_4": "<p><strong>87%</strong> specifically note improvement in the neck and jawline area</p>",
        "ggVHw1Bpvmf_text": "<p>Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A)</p>",
        "ggVxSsSCWX3_text": "<p>Within 18 months, Omnis had become the #1 pharmacist recommendation for men over 40 in Italy. Not through television advertising or celebrity endorsements—through word of mouth among pharmacists and their patients.</p><p><br>Today, the numbers are difficult to ignore:</p>",
        "ggW24EKL39R_text": "<p>The skin on your neck has unique characteristics that make it particularly suited to this three-part approach:</p>",
        "ggX9kCC9axZ_text": "<p>Function: Strengthens and stabilizes new collagen fibers</p>",
        "ggXhf_YZaYi_text": "<p>In the 1980s, Italian dermatological researchers were studying Vitamin A derivatives. They knew that Retinoic Acid—the active form of Vitamin A—was the gold standard for collagen rebuilding. The science was clear.</p><p><br>But they also knew the problem: <strong>Retinoic Acid is too aggressive for most skin.</strong></p><p><br>It works by forcing immediate, rapid cell turnover. For young skin, this is tolerable. For mature skin—especially the thin, sensitive skin of the neck—it's often too much. Redness. Peeling. Inflammation. Damaged moisture barriers.</p><p><br>So they asked: <i>\"What if we could deliver the same collagen-building benefit, but through a gentler pathway?\"</i></p><p><br>The answer was <strong>Retinyl Palmitate.</strong></p>",
        "ggZ9E6xBzUL_text": "<p>These aren't marketing statistics manufactured by an advertising agency. These are outcomes tracked by pharmacists across Italy who recommend this product to their patients and follow up on results.</p>",
        "ggbTuTqebLq_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 1:</span> Absorption</p>",
        "ggdmJEfQCGx_text": "<p>Your fibroblasts begin producing new Type I collagen—the same structural protein that's been degrading since you turned 50. Over 6-8 weeks, this new collagen accumulates, creating visible firming and tightening.</p>",
        "gggEkpXZx3M_text": "\"Costruzione e protezione\"—Building and protecting",
        "ggglynBZ6wJ_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 3:</span> Signaling</p>",
        "ggi_urbOWNu_text": "<p>Hyaluronic Acid</p>",
        "ggj7C6LOfOQ_text": "<p><i>\"What does aging male skin actually need at the cellular level—and how do we deliver it without the side effects?\"</i></p>",
        "gglxA_VI2Ls_text": "<p>This is where most American products fail. They include one active ingredient at a low concentration and call it a day.</p><p><br>Italian pharmaceutical formulation is different. We think in systems.</p><p><br>If you're going to rebuild collagen, you need three things working together:</p>",
        "ggmHrwtgs2f_text": "<p>1. THE BUILDER:</p>",
        "ggsOMXh8XZ2_text": "<p>Here's something most men don't know: newly produced collagen is fragile. It needs to be \"cross-linked\" and stabilized to become strong, durable structural protein.</p><p><br>Vitamin C is the essential cofactor for this process. It's like the difference between wet concrete and cured concrete. Without adequate Vitamin C, your new collagen won't set properly.</p><p><br>But here's the problem: Vitamin C is notoriously unstable. It oxidizes quickly when exposed to air and light. Most Vitamin C products have degraded significantly before they even reach your skin.</p><p><br>Italian labs solved this decades ago using stabilized forms—like Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate—that remain potent until the moment of application. The best formulations use Vitamin C derived from Sicilian blood oranges, which has a unique antioxidant profile.</p>",
        "ggsxYYUhP0l_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 2:</span> Conversion</p>",
        "ggtQn0W-A3k_text": "<p>The Retinoic Acid binds to receptors on your fibroblast cells. These are the \"construction workers\" of your skin. The signal tells them: <i>\"Start building new collagen.\"</i></p>",
        "ggtt2biO-LY_text": "What happened next surprised even me.",
        "ggv66qJ0Hsx_text": "<p>Function: Blocks collagen-destroying enzymes while providing deep hydration</p>",
        "ggvP-hfgjQg_text": "How Retinyl Palmitate works (for the skeptics who want to understand)",
        "ggvslDUYn6k_text": "<p>2. THE REINFORCER:</p>",
        "ggwni7HxvFi_text": "<p>This is where most people misunderstand Hyaluronic Acid.</p><p><br>Yes, it hydrates. Yes, it \"plumps\" fine lines temporarily. But that's not why we include it.</p><p><br>The real function of Hyaluronic Acid in an anti-aging formulation is <strong>enzyme inhibition.</strong></p><p><br>Remember those MMPs I mentioned—the enzymes that break down collagen? Hyaluronic Acid has been shown to inhibit MMP activity. It's actively defending the collagen you're building from being broken down.</p><p><br>Think of it as posting a security guard at the construction site. You're building new structure with Retinyl Palmitate, strengthening it with Vitamin C, and protecting it from demolition with Hyaluronic Acid.</p>",
        "ggz_DcY9K-l_text": "<p>Unlike harsh Retinol that attacks the surface immediately, Retinyl Palmitate absorbs slowly and deeply into the dermis—the structural layer of your skin where collagen actually lives.</p>",
        "section_preload": "true"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-600500557395788437"
    },
    "gp_section_600511340716491339": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "0439b5775baac3a648a44470518afdf3004f23f3b690c9af7ff8b59948e3684f_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg02mqLTMVi_text": "<p>Continued use maintains and builds upon these results. The protective elements prevent degradation while the Retinyl Palmitate continues supporting collagen synthesis.<br><br><i>What you'll notice:</i> Sustained improvement. Some men report continued tightening through month 3-4.</p>",
        "gg07ihRwmmu_text": "<p>New collagen fibers are now accumulating in sufficient quantity to begin affecting surface appearance. The scaffolding is being rebuilt.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>What you'll notice:</i> Early signs of firming. The jawline may appear slightly more defined. The \"crepe\" texture on the neck begins to smooth.</p>",
        "gg1QwEaURQG_text": "<p>\"I'm 58 and I was considering a neck lift. $8,000 minimum, plus recovery time. Decided to try this first because of the guarantee. Eight weeks later, I'm canceling the consultation. The sagging isn't gone completely, but it's reduced enough that I don't feel like I need surgery anymore. That's worth more than $70.\"</p>",
        "gg1yQzRutTJ_text": "<p><strong>Cristiano</strong></p>",
        "gg2CyA24cwm_text": "What to expect, week by week:",
        "gg4QQZ8HQZW_text": "<p><strong>Nick A., Texas</strong></p>",
        "gg4ozl2Y7_g_text": "<p>Week 5-6:</p>",
        "gg4wz_dJQVq_text": "<p>Week 9+:</p>",
        "gg5C2Zi5QvO_text": "<p>\"Super hydrating, absorbs easily, doesn't leave that greasy feeling I hated from other products. But the real change was structural—my neck looks tighter, more defined. My barber asked what I was doing differently.\"</p>",
        "gg6axwv249b_text": "<p>At 54, a sporty but smoking man... my face showed its signs. After about 20 days I started seeing more toned and even skin. By week 8, the sagging along my jawline was noticeably reduced. I waited 40 days to write this review because I wanted to be certain. I'm certain.\"</p>",
        "ggA-hcE2AkG_text": "<p>The Maintenance</p>",
        "ggIG3Zpe_VI_text": "<p>Week 7-8:</p>",
        "ggNVdCO90Ir_text": "<p>The Foundation&nbsp;</p>",
        "ggP7455ZqCd_text": "<p>\"The picture is proof your product works on my 64-year-old face and neck after 2 months use! My collar fits differently now. I don't avoid mirrors anymore.\"</p>",
        "ggQjjX9-kuL_text": "<p>This is when men typically see dramatic visible change. The collagen matrix has been sufficiently rebuilt to create structural improvement that's obvious in the mirror and in photographs.<br><br><i>What you'll notice:</i> Visible tightening of the neck. Improved jawline definition. Reduction in the \"turkey neck\" appearance. Compliments from people who can't quite identify what's different.</p>",
        "ggSlhkCwNVA_text": "<p>\"This product is a game-changer, no joke. Been using the cream for only 15 days and the results are already visible. The skin on my neck feels different—firmer, tighter. Trust me, guys—this is the real deal if you want to look your best without all the fuss.\"</p>",
        "ggTEedFjFHl_text": "<p>\"At 60, my neck skin had relaxed considerably. I was embarrassed to wear open collars. After two months with Omnis, my neck skin is finally firm and toned again. I had feared the retinol because of my sensitive skin—but I had zero problems. My wife noticed before I did.\"</p>",
        "ggUJi1XswRj_text": "<p>The Transformation</p>",
        "ggWh3Q5Ge9p_text": "<p><strong>Giovanni P., 64</strong></p>",
        "ggatAuf9G2Y_text": "<p>\"After spending hundreds on beef tallow creams and every 'men's face cream' I saw advertised on Facebook, this is the first thing that actually works. What beef tallow promised, Omnis actually delivered. My neck is tighter. My jawline is more defined. I'm not invisible anymore.\"</p>",
        "ggclpTSyoSG_text": "<p>Week 3-4:</p>",
        "gggAGkM9rjB_text": "<p>Based on thousands of cases I've tracked, here's the typical progression:</p>",
        "ggj-qf2GbiX_text": "<p><strong>Sergio, 60</strong></p>",
        "ggj9p67_rhZ_text": "Recently, Omnis became available in America.",
        "ggmEUNL5rAC_text": "<p><strong>Luca V., New York</strong></p>",
        "ggnK2SI3GX3_text": "What men are saying about their necks:",
        "ggotoYeaUAa_text": "<p><strong>Robert M., California</strong></p>",
        "ggq3yw4DuJQ_text": "<p>The Emergence</p>",
        "ggrUO1nPsKS_text": "<p>The Retinyl Palmitate is now fully converting to Retinoic Acid within your dermis. Fibroblast activation has begun. New collagen production is underway—you just can't see it yet.<br><br><i>What you'll notice:</i> Skin tone begins to even out. Fine lines appear softer. The texture is visibly improved.</p>",
        "ggvxU3sNQwk_text": "<p><strong>Antonio</strong></p>",
        "ggvyJLS_iR6_text": "<p>Your skin begins to feel different. Smoother. More hydrated. This is the Hyaluronic Acid establishing a protective moisture matrix while the Retinyl Palmitate begins its slow conversion process.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>What you'll notice:</i> Skin feels softer to the touch. Less rough, less dry. People may comment that you \"look rested.\"</p>",
        "ggx1yAL80aD_text": "<p><strong>Davide S., 54</strong></p>",
        "ggx3JVJ5n8b_text": "<p>Week 1-2:</p>",
        "ggxmZhnIjNF_text": "<p>For years, this formulation was only available in European pharmacies. American men who discovered it would buy extra jars whenever they traveled to Italy, or have relatives ship it to them.</p><p><br>Six months ago, the laboratory secured distribution in the United States. And the response from American men has been... significant.</p>",
        "ggzGnRdJ-dv_text": "<p>\"I waited months before buying because I thought it was just another advertising scam. I had tried beef tallow, drugstore creams, even an expensive treatment that cost me €300. Nothing worked on my neck. Finally, real advertising and a product that exceeds expectations. The publicity turned out true.\"</p>",
        "ggzMwWIPout_text": "<p>The Transition&nbsp;</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-600511340716491339"
    },
    "gp_section_600512857544589973": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "9c496084ae16f5c08d50d45911dc65790512a73f47a314d623efb92f54d17b11_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg-IAllCDaZ_text": "<p>4.8 out of 5 | 7,405+ Reviews</p>",
        "gg0Gal3XJzX_text": "<p>You have two paths forward. Both are valid choices. But they lead to very different destinations.</p>",
        "gg2L5Ik6AEj_text": "<p>I always tell my patients: <strong>the 8-week timeline is not arbitrary.</strong></p><p><br>Collagen synthesis is a biological process. It cannot be rushed. Anyone who promises you visible structural change in \"3 days\" or \"one week\" is lying to you. They're selling you temporary surface effects—hydration, mild swelling from irritation—not actual rebuilding.</p><p><br>Real structural change requires real biological time. The men who see the best results are those who trust the process and apply consistently for the full 8 weeks.</p><p><br>This is why I appreciate that Omnis offers their supply in a two-month package. It ensures you have enough product to complete the full transformation cycle without interruption.</p>",
        "gg2Yl7q7q7O_text": "<p><strong>\"The Italian Gentleman Blueprint\"</strong></p>",
        "gg3s9QclLZ__text": "<p>Path 1: Try the Italian Protocol</p>",
        "gg4Zul_tJJH_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"How do I know this will work for MY neck?\"</strong></p>",
        "gg4dXeGg1uU_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\"><strong>FREE Bonus:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>",
        "gg7-ANgD9Wu_text": "A note on patience:",
        "gg9GgQ6tYNM_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"$70 seems expensive for a face cream.\"</strong></p>",
        "ggAGD0WmdLZ_text": "<p>Because Italian pharmaceutical regulations are stricter than American cosmetic regulations.</p><p><br>The FDA classifies most skincare as \"cosmetics,\" which means minimal oversight. Companies can make broad claims with little substantiation. They can include ingredients that are banned in Europe.</p><p><br>Italian pharmaceutical standards require efficacy testing, stability testing, and ingredient purity verification. The formulation process is closer to medicine than makeup.</p><p><br>This isn't nationalism. It's regulatory reality. When I recommend a product to a patient, I need to know it meets pharmaceutical standards—not just marketing standards.</p>",
        "ggAdEtW4dAd_text": "<p>Omnis is currently offering a U.S. launch special that, frankly, makes this decision simple from a cost-benefit perspective.</p><p><br>As a pharmacist, I rarely comment on pricing. But when a formulation of this quality is available at this price point, with a full guarantee, I consider it my professional duty to mention it.</p>",
        "ggAtFdV5M_I_label": "<p>&gt;&gt;&gt; BEGIN THE ITALIAN PROTOCOL — RISK FREE &lt;&lt;&lt;</p>",
        "ggCFkMVyKRV_text": "<p>You don't. Not with certainty. And anyone who guarantees specific results for your specific biology is lying to you.</p><p><br>What I can tell you is this:</p><p><br>The mechanism is sound. Retinyl Palmitate stimulates collagen production. Vitamin C stabilizes that collagen. Hyaluronic Acid protects it from enzymatic breakdown. This is established dermatological science, not speculation.</p><p><br>72,000+ men have used this formulation. 87% report visible improvement in the neck and jawline area. The probability that you'll see meaningful results is high.</p><p><br>But biology is individual. Which is why Omnis offers a 60-day guarantee. You have enough time to complete the full 8-week transformation cycle. If you don't see results, you get your money back.</p><p><br>That's as close to \"risk-free\" as medicine gets.</p>",
        "ggCI_p-QkCE_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Made in Italy 🇮🇹 </strong>— Formulated under strict Italian pharmaceutical regulations</p>",
        "ggCI_p-QkCE_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Approved by Italian Pharmacists </strong>— The #1 recommendation for men over 40</p>",
        "ggCI_p-QkCE_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Dermatologically Tested </strong>— Safe for sensitive skin, including the delicate neck area</p>",
        "ggCI_p-QkCE_childItem_3": "<p><strong>Free From:</strong> Alcohol, parabens, harsh silicones, and 1,600+ ingredients banned under EU pharmaceutical standards</p>",
        "ggCI_p-QkCE_childItem_4": "<p><strong>Night-Only Protocol </strong>— One application, 30 seconds, works while you sleep</p>",
        "ggDZYp1BRpq_text": "<p>Then you've experienced exactly why Retinyl Palmitate exists.</p><p><br>Standard Retinol—and especially prescription Tretinoin—works by forcing rapid, aggressive cell turnover. For mature skin, this is often too much. The irritation causes most men to quit before seeing results.</p><p><br>Retinyl Palmitate converts to the active form <i>inside</i> your skin, gradually, through a two-step enzymatic process. You get the same collagen-building outcome without the surface-level assault.</p><p><br>If harsh Retinol is a sledgehammer, Retinyl Palmitate is a precision instrument. Same destination, gentler path.</p>",
        "ggEOPUHFgxh_text": "<p>$24.99/Bottle</p>",
        "ggFAFK6U4mM_text": "<p>Path 2: Continue as you are</p>",
        "ggG4Fx95u4C_text": "If you're ready to begin the Italian Protocol:",
        "ggGGObA0NQR_text": "<p>Commit to 60 days. Apply Omnis every night before bed. Give the formulation time to work—the full 8 weeks required for collagen rebuilding.</p><p><br>If it works (as it has for 72,000+ men), you'll see visible tightening in your neck. A more defined jawline. The \"turkey neck\" appearance reduced. You'll look in the mirror and see something closer to the man you still feel like inside.</p><p><br>If it doesn't work, you request a refund and you're back where you started—minus nothing except two months of trying.</p><p><br><strong>Your risk:</strong> Zero dollars (with the guarantee)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Your potential outcome:</strong> A neck that doesn't make you self-conscious anymore</p>",
        "ggHFtVBvwoR_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Cold-Pressed Tuscan Olive Oil</strong> — Antioxidant protection against environmental damage</p>",
        "ggHFtVBvwoR_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Hydrolyzed Rice Protein </strong>— Additional anti-aging and moisture-retention support</p>",
        "ggHFtVBvwoR_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Aloe Barbadensis — Soothing, anti-inflammatory base</strong></p>",
        "ggIExn0fks9_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"Why should I trust an Italian product over American brands?\"</strong></p>",
        "ggJjx-cHJf2_text": "<p>— A $40 value. 120 pages on style, presence, and the Italian approach to aging well. (Not required reading, but my patients tell me they appreciate it.)</p>",
        "ggMtiDa3D9f_text": "<p>As a pharmacist, I never recommend a product without understanding the guarantee terms. Here's what Omnis offers:</p><p><br><strong>Try it for 60 days. </strong>That's the full 8-week transformation timeline—enough time for the collagen rebuilding process to produce visible structural change.</p><p><br><strong>If you don't see results, request a full refund.</strong> Contact the support team, explain that you completed the protocol and didn't see the improvement you expected, and receive every penny back.</p><p><br>No \"restocking fees.\" No complicated return authorization process. No interrogation about why you're returning it.</p><p><br><strong>This is how confident they are in the formulation.</strong></p><p><br>In 23 years of pharmacy practice, I've learned that guarantee terms tell you everything about a company's confidence in their product. Companies that offer short windows (14 days, 30 days) know their products don't produce lasting results. They're hoping you'll forget to return it.</p><p><br>A 60-day guarantee on an 8-week protocol means they expect you to complete the full cycle and see results. They're betting on efficacy, not forgetfulness.</p><p><br><strong>Your financial risk: Zero.</strong></p>",
        "ggRnxZc8qvR_text": "Let me be direct with you—as I would be with any patient in my pharmacy.",
        "ggSTYTa2W9N_text": "<p>The Italian Formulation Recommended by Pharmacists Across Europe</p>",
        "ggT0Npug-g4_text": "<p>The Complete Three-Part System in One Application:</p>",
        "ggTLaMg6PdB_text": "<p>Close this page. Go back to your current routine—whether that's nothing, or a moisturizer that isn't working, or occasional consideration of expensive procedures you're not ready to commit to.</p><p><br>Your neck will continue on its current trajectory. Collagen production will continue declining at approximately 1-2% per year. The sagging will progress. The \"turkey neck\" will become more pronounced.</p><p><br>This isn't a scare tactic. It's biology. After 50, this process doesn't reverse itself without intervention.</p><p><br><strong>Your risk:</strong> Zero dollars (today)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Your guaranteed outcome:</strong> Continued structural decline</p>",
        "ggXpxF9En3n_text": "<p>No. And the fact that you're asking tells me you've been burned before.</p><p><br>Here's how to tell the difference: Look at the mechanism.</p><p><br>A moisturizer adds water to the surface. That's all it does. The effects disappear when the water evaporates.</p><p><br>Omnis contains Retinyl Palmitate—a Vitamin A derivative that signals your cells to produce new collagen. This is structural change, not surface hydration. The effects accumulate over time because you're literally rebuilding the scaffolding of your skin.</p><p><br>If a product doesn't contain an active that stimulates collagen synthesis, it's a moisturizer. No matter what the label says.</p>",
        "ggYJJw9Jk3N_text": "<p>Save 64%</p>",
        "ggYOIAlKRp9_text": "U.S. Launch Special: <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Up to 64%OFF</span>",
        "gg_e29wFawP_text": "My professional recommendation:",
        "ggaP2_7nBuH_text": "Omnis Uomo Anti-Aging Night Cream",
        "ggbxLnK9cFV_label": "<p>BEGIN THE ITALIAN PROTOCOL — RISK FREE&nbsp;</p>",
        "ggcXrrxy20x_text": "<p>I don't tell my patients what to do. I give them information and let them decide.</p><p><br>But when they ask me directly—\"Marco, what would you do?\"—I tell them the truth:</p><p><br><strong>I would try it.</strong></p><p><br>Not because it's guaranteed to work for everyone. Nothing in medicine is guaranteed.</p><p><br>But because the mechanism is sound, the risk is zero with the guarantee, and the cost of inaction is watching yourself age in a way that bothers you.</p><p><br>I've seen too many men spend years \"thinking about it\" while their necks continued to sag. They eventually try something—often something more expensive and more invasive—and wish they'd started sooner.</p><p><br>The best time to address structural aging was 10 years ago. The second best time is now.</p><p><br>If you're still reading this, you already know something needs to change. The only question is whether you're ready to find out if this is the solution.</p>",
        "ggeW77cnUjg_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"I&#039;ve tried Retinol before and it destroyed my skin.\"</strong></p>",
        "ggfInSJYpim_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Less than $1.10 per day </strong>— Less than your morning coffee</p>",
        "ggfInSJYpim_childItem_1": "<p><strong>FREE Shipping </strong>— Direct to your door</p>",
        "gggZx6Pt0lx_text": "The <span style=\"color:#0054B4;\">60-Day</span> Clinical Guarantee",
        "gghcLNjCJ6i_text": "<p>That's six full months of supply—enough to complete the entire transformation timeline.</p>",
        "ggiX4t1wA6x_text": "<p><strong>Formulation Standards:</strong></p>",
        "ggih4N2SYCJ_text": "<p>Compared to what?</p><p><br>A drugstore moisturizer that doesn't work? Yes, it's more expensive.</p><p><br>A neck lift consultation? That's $200 just for the appointment. The procedure itself is $5,000-15,000.</p><p><br>Botox for the neck area? $300-600 per session, every 3-4 months. That's $1,200-2,400 per year, indefinitely.</p><p><br>The \"prescription-strength\" Retinol your dermatologist might recommend? $150-300 per tube, plus the office visit.</p><p><br>At $70 for a two-month supply, Omnis costs approximately $1.10 per day. That's less than your morning coffee.</p><p><br>The question isn't whether $70 is expensive. The question is: expensive compared to the alternative? Compared to doing nothing and watching your neck continue to sag?</p><p><br>I've never had a patient tell me they regretted spending $70 on something that worked.</p>",
        "ggmTsojTDn-_text": "So here is the decision, as I present it to my patients:",
        "ggoS3HsedfD_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A) </strong>— The \"gentleman's Retinol.\" Signals fibroblast cells to restart collagen production without the burning, peeling, or irritation of harsh retinoids.</p>",
        "ggoS3HsedfD_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Stabilized Vitamin C from Sicilian Oranges </strong>— Cross-links and strengthens new collagen fibers. Remains potent until moment of application (unlike unstable Vitamin C serums).</p>",
        "ggoS3HsedfD_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Hyaluronic Acid </strong>— Inhibits MMP enzymes that break down collagen. Provides deep hydration while protecting your structural investment.</p>",
        "ggojKT5i0GF_text": "<p>I've spent 23 years helping men navigate the confusing landscape of skincare. I've seen thousands of products come and go. I've watched men waste money on solutions that never had a chance of working.</p><p><br>And I've learned that the men who get results are the ones who stop hoping and start deciding.</p><p><br>So let me give you the same assessment I give to the men who visit my pharmacy in Rome:</p>",
        "ggpqo8bkoQ8_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"What if it doesn&#039;t work? What if I&#039;m wasting my money again?\"</strong></p>",
        "ggqCOAM1KKO_text": "<p><span style=\"color:rgba(5,23,35,0.5);\"><s>$69.99</s></span></p>",
        "ggu3gqC17Qk_text": "<p>Then you return it and get every penny back.</p><p><br>Omnis offers a 60-day money-back guarantee. Not 30 days—60. That's specifically because the transformation timeline requires 8 weeks. They're giving you enough time to complete the full cycle before you decide.</p><p><br>If you don't see visible improvement in your neck by week 8, you contact their support team and receive a full refund. No complicated process. No \"restocking fees.\" No interrogation.</p><p><br>You're not risking $70. You're risking nothing except the time it takes to find out if this works for you.</p><p><br>And if it does work? You've solved a problem that's been bothering you every time you look in the mirror.</p>",
        "gguhiXK5BzI_childItem_0": "<p><strong>\"Is this just another expensive moisturizer?\"</strong></p>",
        "ggvfg6mMD2k_text": "<p><i>Supporting Ingredients:</i></p>",
        "ggxPndph-D0_text": "The questions men ask me (and my honest answers):"
      },
